article.description: James Webb III and Anthony Drmic each scored 22 points, and Boise State topped 100 points for the first time since 2013 in a 101-81 win over Northern Arizona on Monday.
article.headline: Boise State tops Northern Arizona 101-81
article.story: BOISE, Idaho -- James Webb III and Anthony Drmic each scored 22 points, and Boise State topped 100 points for the first time since 2013 in a 101-81 win over Northern Arizona on Monday. Boise State (1-1) led 47-44 at halftime, but the Broncos quickly pushed it to double digits and led by 25 with 9:18 to play. Webb III made 9 of 14 shots and grabbed 11 rebounds. Drmic was 6 of 9 from the field, including 4 of 7 from beyond the arc. Chandler Hutchison had career highs of 12 points and 11 rebounds, and Mikey Thompson added 17 points and five assists. Drmic had 23 points in a loss to Montana on Friday. Jaleni Neely had 20 points for Northern Arizona (0-2) and Kris Yanku added 10 points with eight assists. The teams combined to make 24 3-pointers.
